cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with content delivery in caching networks, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method through numerical examples, which involves simulations and experiments, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible categories. Finally, the paper proposes an adaptive method for content delivery, which involves coding techniques, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
